# AI/ML Service — AtlasOS Agent Rules

## Model Safety
- All models must be registered in the Model Risk Register before deployment.
- All model outputs must include: confidence_score, ai_generated flag, and contributing_factors.
- Clinical models require CMO approval for production deployment.

## Data Handling
- Never use real patient data for training without de-identification.
- All data pipelines must have lineage tracking (source → transform → output).
- Embeddings must not contain recoverable PHI.

## Testing
- Bias testing required across: age, sex, race/ethnicity, language, SES, disability.
- Benchmark evaluation against published baselines before deployment.
- Shadow deployment required for 72 hours before production.

## Monitoring
- Drift detection: 5% alert threshold, 10% auto-disable threshold.
- Alert fatigue: Track alert-to-action ratio, target > 20%.

## Autonomous Operations
- Auto-run benchmarks on model updates.
- Auto-create bias test reports for new model versions.
- Auto-rollback models that exceed drift thresholds.
